HEADWORD: brisant
<hw>bri"sant</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>of or pertaining to
brisance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>having the ability to shatter, as contrasted with
merely fracturing; -- of explosives.</def> <note>the more brisant
explosives, such as dynamite, will shatter rock into smaller fragments
than the less brisant, such as gunpowder.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

